From:Spekulatius
OT re Chase Card -
I remember reading a letter from Chase regarding payment deferral option a
while ago. Like all those letters that offer something like thise (insurance
etc.) it went straight into the waste basked.

I do like my Chase Businesscard (even though I don't have a business LOL) for
the discount points (3% gas, 3% home improvement 1% everything else) but they
are not a company that you want to mess around with. Chase is one of the
toughest companies in terms of shutting accounts down and they are not known to
give away free money - in fact they were one of the worst in terms of
exploiting the 2 cycle billing that is now banned in Obama's credit card bill.

If you want a good and trouble free credit card - join the PenFed credit Union
for example and get their discount card - 5% cash back on gas and 1.25% on
everything else is hard to beat. Despite the affiliation everybody can join via
when you buy membership for a year (and small fee) to some sort of
military/veteran organization (via Penfeds website). Penfed is one of the best
credit unions overall, IMO.
